Text: Context: This project is to create a solution for the Southern District Health Board that will allow them to easily update their senior doctors salaries.

The salaries are updated when: It's the anniversary of their fellowshipAnnual pay increase through their newly agreed upon MECA (Multi Employer Collective Agreement)When a doctor joins or leaves a team (the whole teams on-call hours thus their pay gets adjusted)It is preferable to have as many of these processes automated as possible.
Currently this is all updated manually, with each doctor having an individual excel spreadsheet that needs updating.
This makes it easy to miss someone if you had to update, lets say a team of 40 people.
We started off this week with meeting Milair for our client meeting.
There were many details to go over for this project which could quite easily get out of hand if we aren't careful.
I think we have a decent grasp of the problem at hand and we should be able to produce something to provide some value to the client.
We did some research and found out that some of the other district health boards are also using excel spread sheets for their REM schedules.
Further inquiries could also be made to the health boards we haven't heard from yet.
We should also continue researching other software solutions and check that such a product doesn't already exist.
Our current plan is to create a C# desktop application using WPF (windows presentation foundation).
Having a MySQL relational database to store and group the doctors into their teams.

We need to be very certain that the results of our solution are accurate, if it's not it could potentially cost the client a lot of money, so we need to ensure proper testing is done throughout the life-cycle of development.

This week, besides the work on the poster, I started working on the ERD for the database, trying to make it as flexible as possible so that it would accommodate the many edge-cases of how salaries are updated.

I have no doubt the ERD will continue to evolve over the life-cycle of the project as we discover more edge-cases or realize that some have been missed out but currently we think this covers enough for us to start working and testing on.
Plans for the next week: Paper prototyping the UI and have it tested by MilairStart forming the databaseIf paper prototyping goes well then start implementing the UI
